data.chText: （事物名称不详、无关紧要或所指事物明显时用）东西，物品，玩意儿
data.enText: used to refer to a substance, material, group of objects, etc. when you do not know the name, when the name is not important or when it is obvious what you are talking about

data.chText: 地毯上那黏乎乎的都是什么玩意儿？
data.enText: What's all that sticky stuff on the carpet?

data.chText: 椅子都包了一种塑料膜。
data.enText: The chairs were covered in some sort of plastic stuff.

data.chText: 这酒不错。
data.enText: This wine is good stuff.

data.chText: 我不明白你怎么能吃那种东西！
data.enText: I don't know how you can eat that stuff!

data.chText: 他们出售文具之类的东西。
data.enText: They sell stationery and stuff (like that) .

data.chText: 我那些东西都哪儿去了？
data.enText: Where's all my stuff (= my possessions) ?

data.chText: 请你把桌上那些玩意儿全都拿走好不好？
data.enText: Could you move all that stuff off the table?

data.chText: （泛指）活儿，话，念头，东西
data.enText: used to refer in a general way to things that people do, say, think, etc.

data.chText: 我今天有好多事儿要做。
data.enText: I've got loads of stuff to do today.

data.chText: 我喜欢看书什么的。
data.enText: I like reading and stuff .

data.chText: 这支乐队首张专辑有几支很棒的曲子。
data.enText: The band did some great stuff on their first album.

data.chText: 这一切都不错，干得漂亮！
data.enText: This is all good stuff . Well done!

data.chText: 哪来的什么“史密斯夫人”那一套？叫我安娜好了。
data.enText: What's all this ‘Mrs Smith’ stuff? Call me Anna.

data.chText: 我不信什么鬼呀魂呀的。
data.enText: I don't believe in all that stuff about ghosts.

data.chText: 基本特征；特质；根本；基础；原料

data.enText: or
the most important feature of sth; something that sth else is based on or is made from

data.chText: 那是一次奇妙的旅行，宛如梦境。
data.enText: The trip was magical; the stuff of which dreams are made.

data.chText: 游行示威是那一地区政治生活的基本内容。
data.enText: Parades and marches were the very stuff of politics in the region.

data.chText: 我们来看看你是怎样一个人。
data.enText: Let's see what stuff you're made of (= what sort of person you are).
do your stuff

data.chText: 施展自己的本事；露一手
data.enText: to do what you are good at or what you have been trained to do

data.chText: 队中几名成员压根儿没有使出自己的本事。
data.enText: Some members of the team are just not doing their stuff (= doing as well as they should) .

data.chText: 这药显然起作用了。
data.enText: The medicine has clearly done its stuff.
not give a stuff

data.chText: 一点不在乎
data.enText: to not care at all about sth
stuff and nonsense

data.chText: 废话；胡说八道
data.enText: used by some people to say that they think that sth is stupid or not true
know your stuff

data.chText: 精通业务；对工作很内行
data.enText: to know a lot about a particular subject or job
be made of sterner stuff

data.chText: 性格十分坚强；有很大的毅力
data.enText: to have a stronger character and to be more determined in dealing with problems than other people
strut your stuff

data.chText: （尤指在跳舞或表演时）卖弄自己那一套，露一手
data.enText: to proudly show your ability, especially at dancing or performing
don't sweat the small stuff

data.chText: 不要为鸡毛蒜皮的事伤脑筋
data.enText: used to tell sb not to worry about small details or unimportant things

data.chText: 填满；装满；塞满；灌满
data.enText: to fill a space or container tightly with sth

data.chText: 她得在500个信封里装上传单。
data.enText: She had 500 envelopes to stuff with leaflets.

data.chText: 她得把500份传单装进信封里。
data.enText: She had 500 leaflets to stuff into envelopes.

data.chText: 冰箱满得都快撑破了。
data.enText: The fridge is stuffed to bursting.

data.chText: 所有抽屉里都放满了信函文件。
data.enText: All the drawers were stuffed full of letters and papers.

data.chText: 把…塞进（或填进）
data.enText: to push sth quickly and carelessly into a small space

data.chText: 她把钱塞到软垫底下。
data.enText: She stuffed the money under a cushion.

data.chText: 他两手插在口袋里。
data.enText: His hands were stuffed in his pockets.

data.chText: 在（蔬菜、鸡等）里填入（另外一种食物）；给…装馅
data.enText: to fill a vegetable, chicken, etc. with another type of food

data.chText: 你打算给火鸡加填料吗？
data.enText: Are you going to stuff the turkey?

data.chText: 酿柿子椒
data.enText: stuffed peppers

data.chText: （使）吃撑，吃足，吃得过饱
data.enText: to eat a lot of food or too much food; to give sb a lot or too much to eat

data.chText: 他坐在桌前大吃大嚼。
data.enText: He sat at the table stuffing himself.

data.chText: 正餐前不要给孩子一个劲地吃巧克力。
data.enText: Don't stuff the kids with chocolate before their dinner.

data.chText: 我们在聚会时都吃撑了。
data.enText: We stuffed our faces at the party.

data.chText: 制作（动物）标本
data.enText: to fill the dead body of an animal with material and preserve it, so that it keeps its original shape and appearance

data.chText: 他们请人把他们的宠物狗制成了标本。
data.enText: They had had their pet dog stuffed.
get stuffed

data.chText: 滚开；不稀罕
data.enText: used to tell sb in a rude and angry way to go away, or that you do not want sth
stuff it

data.chText: （表示改变了主意或不在乎）管它呢，去它的
data.enText: used to show that you have changed your mind about sth or do not care about sth

data.chText: 我本来没想在剧中扮演角色，然后又一想——管它呢——干吗不演？
data.enText: I didn't want a part in the play, then I thought─stuff it─why not?
you, etc. can stuff sth

data.chText: （粗暴或气愤地拒绝）还是收起你的宝贝吧
data.enText: used to tell sb in a rude and angry way that you do not want sth

data.chText: 我告诉他们说我不稀罕他们的工作。
data.enText: I told them they could stuff their job.

data.text: things ♦ stuff ♦ possessions ♦ junk ♦ belongings ♦ goods ♦ valuables

data.chText: 以上各词均指东西、物品，尤指个人拥有或随身携带的物件。
data.enText: These are all words for objects or items, especially ones that you own or have with you at a particular time.
things

data.chText: 指个人拥有或作特定用途的物品、衣服、用具：
data.enText: ( rather informal ) objects, clothing or tools that you own or that are used for a particular purpose

data.chText: 我帮你打点行装好吗？
data.enText: Shall I help you pack your things?

data.chText: 随身带上游泳用品。
data.enText: Bring your swimming things.
stuff

data.chText: 指名称不详、名称无关紧要或所指明确的东西、物品、玩意儿：
data.enText: [U] ( informal ) used to refer to a group of objects when you do not know their names, when the names are not important or when it is obvious what you are talking about

data.chText: 我那些东西都哪儿去了？
data.enText: Where's all my stuff?
possessions

data.chText: 指个人财产、私人物品，尤指动产：
data.enText: things that you own, especially sth that can be moved

data.chText: 囚犯除信件和照片外不允许有任何私人物品。
data.enText: Prisoners were allowed no personal possessions except letters and photographs.
junk

data.chText: 指无用的东西、无价值的东西：
data.enText: [U] things that are considered useless or of little value

data.chText: 我把阁楼里所有的废旧杂物都清除干净了。
data.enText: I've cleared out all that old junk from the attic.
belongings

data.chText: 指动产，尤指随身物品：
data.enText: possessions that can be moved, especially ones that you have with you at a particular time

data.chText: 请确保在下飞机前带好所有的随身物品。
data.enText: Please make sure you have all your belongings with you when leaving the plane.
goods

data.chText: 指动产、（可搬运的）私人财产：
data.enText: ( rather formal or technical ) possessions that can be moved

data.chText: 他被判犯销赃罪。
data.enText: He was found guilty of handling stolen goods .
valuables

data.chText: 尤指私人的贵重物品（如首饰、相机等）：
data.enText: things that are worth a lot of money, especially small personal things such as jewellery or cameras

data.chText: 现金或其他贵重物品请勿乱放。
data.enText: Never leave cash or other valuables lying around.
personal things/stuff/possessions/belongings
worldly possessions/belongings/goods
to collect/gather/pack (up) your/the things/stuff/possessions/belongings
to go through/look through/search sb's/your/the things/stuff/possessions/belongings

means: (事物名称不详、无关紧要或所指事物明显时用)物品
在(蔬菜、鸡等)里填入(另外一种食物)

ex.chText: 杯子里装满了牛奶。
ex.enText: The glass is filled with milk.

ex.chText: 我的工作是把米袋子装满。
ex.enText: My job is to fill the rice sacks.

ex.chText: 她精彩的演讲让礼堂爆满。
ex.enText: Her excellent speech filled the auditorium.

ex.chText: 我对她充满敬佩之情。
ex.enText: I am filled with admiration for her.

synonyms.bx: 指（使）容器等装满某物或处所等挤满人；也可引申指使某人充满某种感情。

ex.chText: 他把袋子装满了书。
ex.enText: He crammed his bag with books.

ex.chText: 我们都挤了进去，然后他发动了汽车。
ex.enText: We all crammed in and he started the car.

ex.chText: 图书馆里挤满了读者。
ex.enText: The library was crammed with readers.

synonyms.bx: 指把某物塞入狭小的空间；也指人挤进或挤满某一交通工具、处所等。

ex.chText: 他的救生衣未能充气胀起来。
ex.enText: His life jacket failed to inflate.

ex.chText: 他花1到2分钟就可以把这个气球吹好。
ex.enText: It takes him 1-2 minutes to inflate this balloon.

ex.chText: 你需要多长时间才能把橡皮筏充好气？
ex.enText: How long do you need to inflate the dinghy?

synonyms.bx: 指某物充气膨胀，或指为某物充气。

ex.chText: 这个枕头里塞满了棉花。
ex.enText: The pillow is stuffed with cotton.

ex.chText: 她无法搬动那些装满书的箱子。
ex.enText: She can't move those boxes stuffed full of books.

ex.chText: 你给火鸡填料了吗？
ex.enText: Did you stuff the turkey?

synonyms.bx: 指把某物装满；用于烹饪时则指给鸡、辣椒等填馅。

ex.chText: 作为一种建筑材料，木材不够结实。
ex.enText: As a building material, wood is not sturdy enough.

ex.chText: 由于缺少原料，生产已陷入停顿。
ex.enText: Production has come to a halt owing to the lack of raw materials.

ex.chText: 他正在为写一部传记收集素材。
ex.enText: He is now collecting material for a biography.

synonyms.bx: 尤指木材、石头、金属、塑料等用于制作某物的原材料；也可指文学创作的素材。

ex.chText: 整个宇宙是由各种物质构成的。
ex.enText: The entire universe is made up of different kinds of matter.

ex.chText: 该湖中有丰富的有机物质。
ex.enText: The lake is rich in organic matter.

ex.chText: 物质是第一性的，精神是第二性的。
ex.enText: Matter is primary and mind is secondary.

synonyms.bx: 一切有形物质的总称，既指构成宇宙万物的物质，也指哲学上与意识相对的物质。

ex.chText: 我裤子上粘了些黏糊糊的东西。
ex.enText: There is some sticky stuff on my trousers.

ex.chText: 把所有的东西都放进盒子里，再用胶带封好。
ex.enText: Put all the stuff into the box and seal it tightly with sticky tape.

ex.chText: 请你把桌子上的那些玩意儿全部清走行不行？
ex.enText: Could you move all the stuff off the desk?

synonyms.bx: 多用于日常口语，可指各种叫不出名称的物质、材料、物体等；有时指无关紧要的东西，含轻视意味。

ex.chText: 土壤由各种化学物质组成。
ex.enText: Soil consists of various chemical substances.

ex.chText: 水、冰和蒸汽是形态不同的同一物质。
ex.enText: Water, ice and steam are the same substance in different forms.

ex.chText: 警察在他的公文包里发现了违禁品。
ex.enText: Police found an illegal substance in his briefcase.

synonyms.bx: 通常指有某种特性的固体、液体或气体物质。

tr: unspecified qualities required to do or be something
example: the stuff of heros
you don't have the stuff to be a United States Marine

tr: a critically important or characteristic component
example: suspense is the very stuff of narrative
don't give me that stuff
it was stuff I had heard before
there's good stuff in that book
did you take all your clobber?

tr: the tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object
example: coal is a hard black material
wheat is the stuff they use to make bread

tr: fill with a stuffing while cooking
example: Have you stuffed the turkey yet?
stuff a pillow with feathers

tr: treat with grease, fill, and prepare for mounting
example: stuff a bearskin
She stuffed herself at the dinner
The kids binged on ice cream
My nose is all stuffed
Her arteries are blocked
The child stuffed candy into his pockets
Stuff money into an envelope
She thrust the letter into his hand

value.def: You can use stuff to refer to things such as a substance, a collection of things, events, or ideas, or the contents of something in a general way without mentioning the thing itself by name.

example.ex: I'd like some coffee, and I don't object to the powdered stuff if it's all you've got...
example.tran: 我想来点咖啡，如果你只有速溶的那种也可以。

example.ex: I don't know anything about this antique stuff...
example.tran: 我对于这种古玩物件一无所知。

example.ex: 'What do you want to know?'—'About life and stuff.'...
example.tran: “你想知道些什么？”——“关于生命之类的东西。”

example.ex: Don't tell me you still believe in all that stuff?...
example.tran: 别告诉我你仍旧相信那些东西。

example.ex: He pointed to a duffle bag.'That's my stuff.'
example.tran: 他指着一个旅行袋说：“那是我的东西。”

value.def: If you stuff something somewhere, you push it there quickly and roughly.

example.ex: I stuffed my hands in my pockets...
example.tran: 我把手插进口袋里。

example.ex: He stuffed the newspapers into a litter bin and headed down the street...
example.tran: 他把报纸塞进了垃圾箱，然后沿街往前走了。

example.ex: His pants were stuffed inside the tops of his boots.
example.tran: 他的裤腿儿塞在靴子里。

value.def: If you stuff a container or space with something, you fill it with something or with a quantity of things until it is full.

example.ex: He grabbed my purse, opened it and stuffed it full, then gave it back to me...
example.tran: 他抢过我的钱包，打开并塞满钱，然后还给了我。

example.ex: He still stood behind his cash register stuffing his mouth with popcorn.
example.tran: 他仍站在收银机后，嘴里塞满了爆米花。

example.ex: ...wallets stuffed with dollars.
example.tran: 装满美元的钱包

value.def: If you stuff yourself, you eat a lot of food.

example.ex: I could stuff myself with ten chocolate bars and half an hour later eat a big meal.
example.tran: 我可以一口气吃10块巧克力，半小时后再吃一顿大餐。

example.ex: But you're just so stuffed you won't be able to drink anything.
example.tran: 但你已经撑得什么也喝不下了。

value.def: If you stuff a bird such as a chicken or a vegetable such as a pepper, you put a mixture of food inside it before cooking it.

example.ex: Will you stuff the turkey and shove it in the oven for me?
example.tran: 你能帮我给火鸡填上料然后放进烤箱里吗？

example.ex: ...stuffed tomatoes.
example.tran: 酿西红柿

value.tran: 给…装馅儿;给(鸡、辣椒等食物里)加填料

value.def: If a dead animal is stuffed, it is filled with a substance so that it can be preserved and displayed.

example.ex: A pike weighing 29 lb 8 oz taken in 1878 was stuffed and is on display at the estate office...
example.tran: 一条 1878 年捕获的重 29 磅 8 盎司的梭子鱼被制成标本陈列在庄园管理处。

example.ex: He didn't much care for the stuffed animal heads that hung on the walls.
example.tran: 他不是很喜欢墙上挂的那些动物头颅标本。

value.def: If you say that one thing is the stuff of another, you mean that the first thing is a very important feature or characteristic of the second thing, or that the second thing can be based or built on the first thing.

example.ex: The idea that we can be whatever we want has become the stuff of television commercials.
example.tran: 每个人皆无所不能，这一理念已经成为电视广告的精髓。

value.tran: 基本特征;特质;根本;基础

value.def: If you are angry with someone for something that they have said or done, you might say 'Get stuffed!' to them.
Stuff is used in front of nouns to emphasize that you do not care about something, or do not want it.

example.ex: Ultimately my attitude was: stuff them...
example.tran: 我最终的态度是：去他们的。

example.ex: Stuff your money. We don't want a handout.
example.tran: 收起你的钱，我们不需要施舍。

value.tran: (用在名词前表示强调)不稀罕，不在乎

value.def: If you do your stuff, you perform an activity in the way that people expect.

example.ex: Once I get on the pitch I know I can do my stuff...
example.tran: 我一上场就知道是我大显身手的时候了。

example.ex: All that was left was to plant the roses and wait for nature to do her stuff.
example.tran: 剩下的就只是栽上玫瑰，然后等大自然施展她的神奇魔力。

value.tran: 露一手;施展自己的本事

value.def: If you say that someone knows their stuff, you mean that they are good at doing something because they know a lot about it.

example.ex: These chaps know their stuff after seven years of war.
example.tran: 7年的战争过后，这些家伙都成了作战行家。

trans: 性感的人；艳情电影(或书籍等)；技艺很高的人；高手
小东西；区区小事；小绳索；小事
